text:
Node (or v8) never reclaims unrefed udp sockets

This happens in node versions 8 to 12:

```
 var p = require('process')
 var net = require('net')
 var udp = require('dgram')

 var iter = 0

 while (true) {
 iter++
 if (iter % 10000 === 0) {
 var mu = p.memoryUsage()
 console.log({ rss: mu.rss / 1024 / 1024, iter })
 }

 // { rss: 34.765625, iter: 4520000 } 
 //var s = net.Socket() 

 // { rss: 976.6484375, iter: 1160000 } 
 var u = udp.createSocket('udp4')
 }
```

In the tcp test, sockets remain at a constant size of RSS, with udp, they grow in linear size - this appears that the udp created sockets are never being removed/gc'ed?

